entry.sense:
1. nadaHahu, 
aor. _a {yanodaHu}, (A, Ḳ,) inf. n. nadoHN; 
and nd-Hhu↓, (A,) inf. n. tanodiyHN; (TA;) He made it (a place, A) spacious, roomy, wide, or ample. (A, Ḳ.)

It has been asserted that n and r do not come together in any [pure] Arabic word; and F has said the same in art. nrX; 
[or rather he has there said that r does not occur in an Arabic word with n before it; (meaning a radical n;)] 
yet he has here mentioned this word as though it were pure Arabic. So says MF. To this it may be replied, that I is inserted to separate the n and r, as remarked in the L. (TA.)

nayorabN, 
fem. with p {nayorabapN}; 
and cuw nayorabK; A mischievous man; (Ḳ;) one who utters malicious and mischievous misrepresentations, calumnies, or slanders. (TA.)

