Also, A certain vein lying within the Sulob [i. e. backbone, or back], beneath the [portion of flesh and sinew called the] maton; 
and so Aln-aAYiTu↓: (Ḳ:) or the latter is a vein extending in, or along, the Sulob, 
[in some copies of the Ḳ, qalob, which, as is said in the TA, is a mistake,] by the cutting of which the maSofuwr [or person in whose belly is yellow water, as explained in the TA,] is treated for the purpose of cure. (Ṣ, Ḳ.)

